<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pacheco</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Guatemala and Honduras</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-29"><hi rend="italic">September
                                    29, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received October 17.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your instruction No. 21, of August 22, and to report that I have addressed a
                        communication to the minister of foreign relations on the subject of the <hi rend="italic">Colima</hi> arms, strictly in accordance with your
                        instructions.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. Pacheco</hi>.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>